article.headline: Florida St. 78, Gardner-Webb 53
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Chris Singleton scored a career-high 30 points and Deividas Dulkys added 12 points as Florida State defeated Gardner-Webb 78-53 on Tuesday night. Singleton was 10 of 11 from the floor and added 12 rebounds. "This is about as good a stat line as you're going to see," Florida State coach Leonard Hamilton said. "That's a big-time night in anybody's book." Singleton, a junior forward, scored 15 of the Seminoles' first 25 points. "I just got in the rhythm of the game," Singleton said. "When I thought I had an open shot, I just took it." Singleton had a career scoring night just two days after he recorded a triple-double against UNC Greensboro on Sunday. His triple-double -- 22 points, 11 rebounds and 10 steals -- was just the third in FSU history. Florida State (3-0) outrebounded Gardner-Webb 40-28. The Seminoles shot 49.1 percent from the field (26 of 53) and hit 7 of 15 3-pointers (46.7 percent). Jonathan Moore had 21 points -- knocking down 5 of 8 3-point shots -- and Laron Buggs added 11 points for Gardner-Webb (2-1), which shot just 35.2 percent from the floor (19 of 54). The Bulldogs had 18 turnovers and nine assists. Singleton's previous career-high was 23 in a win over Georgia Tech in January. "I don't know how many people have a guy like him -- not many," Gardner-Webb coach Chris Holtmann said.
